  "id": "Hackney-2024_2240",
  "decision_conditions": [
    "&lt;p&gt;&lt;span id=&quot;docs-internal-guid-dfdc90e8-7fff-aee4-2f94-6ca401a8407e&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 10.5pt; font-family: Arial, sans-serif; background-color: transparent; font-variant-numeric: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; font-variant-alternates: normal; font-variant-position: normal; font-variant-emoji: normal; vertical-align: baseline; white-space-collapse: preserve;&quot;&gt;In the absence of a Unilateral Undertaking or a Section 106 agreement securing appropriate mitigation by restricting future occupiers of the development from obtaining parking permits within the Controlled Parking Zone the proposed development would likely exacerbate existing parking stress and congestion on the surrounding highway network. The application is, therefore, contrary to Policy LP45 of the Hackney Local Plan 2033 (2020) and Policy T6 of the London Plan (2021). &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;",
    "&lt;p&gt;&lt;span id=&quot;docs-internal-guid-8027f40f-7fff-43bb-e363-99e8dcbf9310&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 10.5pt; font-family: Arial, sans-serif; background-color: transparent; font-variant-numeric: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; font-variant-alternates: normal; font-variant-position: normal; font-variant-emoji: normal; vertical-align: baseline; white-space-collapse: preserve;&quot;&gt;In the absence of a legal agreement securing the financial contribution towards carbon off-setting has not been submitted or completed, the proposal would therefore fail to secure sufficient energy efficiency measures and/or financial contribution towards carbon offsetting, the proposed development would result in an unacceptable level of carbon dioxide emissions, contrary to Policy LP55 of the Hackney Local Plan 2033 (2020).&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;",
    "&lt;p&gt;&lt;span id=&quot;docs-internal-guid-86a0cda4-7fff-0d24-bea7-3b0b8a275701&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-variant-numeric: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; font-variant-alternates: normal; font-variant-position: normal; font-variant-emoji: normal; vertical-align: baseline;&quot;&gt;By reason of the proposed floorspace failing to meet the minimum internal space standards in terms of floor area, and failing to provide dual-aspect accommodation, the proposed development would result in the provision of substandard accommodation. The proposed dwelling would, therefore, fail to provide high quality accommodation and, thus, would be contrary to Policy D6 of the London Plan (2021) and Policy LP17 of the Hackney Local Plan 2033 (2020).&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;",
    "&lt;p&gt;&lt;span id=&quot;docs-internal-guid-a55555f8-7fff-8682-73fe-f2fac43cd135&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-variant-numeric: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; font-variant-alternates: normal; font-variant-position: normal; font-variant-emoji: normal; vertical-align: baseline;&quot;&gt;The proposed development, by reason of a lack of provision of affordable housing, would fail to adequately contribute towards the provision of mixed and balanced communities and housing needs in the local area. As such, the development would not be consistent with Policies H4 and H5 of the London Plan (2021), Policies LP12 and LP13 of the LP33, and the Hackney &lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-variant-numeric: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; font-variant-alternates: normal; font-variant-position: normal; font-variant-emoji: normal; vertical-align: baseline;&quot;&gt;S106 Planning Contributions Supplementary Planning Document (2020)&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-variant-numeric: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; font-variant-alternates: normal; font-variant-position: normal; font-variant-emoji: normal; vertical-align: baseline;&quot;&gt;.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;",
    "&lt;span id=&quot;docs-internal-guid-098da0da-7fff-5d82-3a0f-f9fbb01f37ce&quot;&gt;&lt;p dir=&quot;ltr&quot; style=&quot;line-height:1.2;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 10.5pt; font-family: Arial, sans-serif; background-color: transparent; font-variant-numeric: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; font-variant-alternates: normal; font-variant-position: normal; font-variant-emoji: normal; vertical-align: baseline; white-space-collapse: preserve;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-family: &amp;quot;PT Sans&amp;quot;, &amp;quot;Helvetica Neue&amp;quot;, Helvetica, Arial, sans-serif;&quot;&gt;The proposed development, by reason of its bulk, massing, scale, detailed design, position and location, would result in an incongruous and incompatible form of development that would have a detrimental impact upon the character, appearance and significance of the Grade II Listed Building and Stoke Newington Conservation Area. &lt;/span&gt;The harm is assessed to be less than substantial to the designated heritage assets which triggers paragraph 215 of the National Planning Policy Framework (2024) requiring the harm to be weighed against the public benefits of the proposals. In this instance there are minor public benefits in creating an additional residential unit. However, this benefit is not considered to outweigh the harm to the listed building. The proposed development would, therefore, conflict with Policy HC1 of the London Plan (2021), Policy LP3 of the Hackney Local Plan (2020) and the National Planning Policy Framework (2024).&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;div&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 10.5pt; font-family: Arial, sans-serif; background-color: transparent; font-variant-numeric: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; font-variant-alternates: normal; font-variant-position: normal; font-variant-emoji: normal; vertical-align: baseline; white-space-collapse: preserve;&quot;&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/span&gt;"
  ],
